   Lobbyist Ethics Course Feb. 7
   The Assembly and Senate ethics committees have scheduled ethics courses
   for lobbyists on February 7 and August 2, 2002. Call the Senate at
   (916) 324-6929 for more information.
   Workshops Scheduled for Feb. 2002
   The FPPC puts on workshops and seminars around the state for filing
   officers and officials receiving the SEI (form 700). There are 7 of
   these workshops scheduled for February 2002. To find the session
   nearest you, check the workshop and seminar schedules by clicking here.
   Sacramento Workshops
   The FPPC will offer workshops for SEI filing officers at FPPC
   headquarters Feb. 5 & 14 (city/county agencies); Feb. 7 & 20 (state
   agencies); and Feb. 13 (multi-county agencies). Click here for further
   details.
   Workshops Outside Sacramento
   Additional SEI workshops for city/county agencies are scheduled for
   Pasadena on February 6 and San Jose on February 25 (click here).
   Summary Judgment in Pro-Life Lawsuit
   A federal district court has granted summary judgment to the
   defendants--the FPPC and the California Attorney General--in California
   Pro-life Council PAC v. Karen Getman, et. al. The decision is here. The
   press release is here. For an update on litigation involving the FPPC,
   click here.
   IP Meeting on Lobbying Disclosure 2/1/02
   The FPPC will hold an Interested Persons meeting to discuss lobbying
   disclosure and implementation of Chapter 921, Stats. 2001 (AB 1325).
   The meeting is scheduled for 10:00 a.m. on February 1, 2002. The agenda
   is here.
   New Fact Sheet for E-530 (Issue Advocacy Form)
   The FPPC has released a fact sheet with information about the new form
   E-530, used to report issue advocacy expenditures for communications
   identifying candidates. The fact sheet is here.
   No February Meeting
   The Fair Political Practices Commission will not meet in February 2002.
   The date of the next meeting of the FPPC is March 14, 2001. See the
   Schedule of Upcoming Meetings page for more meeting dates.
   Getting Advice
   The new FPPC booklet "How Do I Get Advice From the FPPC?" is now
   available here.
   Conflicts Slide Presentation Now On Web
   An on-line slide presentation detailing regulatory changes to
   conflicts-of-interest law is available here.
   SEI Overview Available on Web
   The FPPC has published a new 9-page color pamphlet describing state
   economic disclosure law and reporting requirements for public
   officials. For a copy of "Your Duty to File" click here.
   Prop. 34
   For a chart showing Prop. 34's changes to campaign finance laws,
   updated to show SB 34 changes, click here. For information on
   Interested Persons meetings, click here. To see the latest press
   release, click here.

